From the manufacturer

The DJ controller for Android or iOS smartphones

Designed for Algoriddim djay: the DJ app for mixing on a smartphone or tablet.

Easy wireless connection via Bluetooth.

Mix using music streaming services

DJControl Mix lets you mix music tracks stored on your smartphone or tablet, orusing one of the music streaming services built into djay: SoundCloud and TIDAL. You can even use Beatport LINK and Beatsource LINK with iOS.

(Music streaming service subscriptions are required)

Smartphone stand included

Works with smartphones and tablets, with or without a cover.

Foldable and non-slip.

Monitor tracks using the included DJ splitter cable

To create great mixes, DJs listen to (i.e.monitor) upcoming tracks on their headphones. They make sure that both the outgoing and incoming tracks work well together, andadjust the speed of one of the tracks (if necessary) before starting to transition between them.

Read more

ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

Connect wirelessly to your smartphone via Bluetooth. Powered via USB, either connected to a power adapter or external battery so that you can mix anywhere!

Scratch using the touch-detecting jog wheels and browse your tracks. Latency is imperceptible thanks to Bluetooth Low Energy technology.

Customize your mix with effects, Hot Cues and samples. Easily create great transitions using the volume and filter/bass knobs, the crossfader

Read more

Mode 1: Start mixing quickly via Bluetooth

1. Enable Bluetooth.

2. (Optional) Connect your speaker to your smartphone via Bluetooth.

3. Connect DJControl Mix to an external battery or power adapter.

4. Connect DJControl Mix to your smartphone via the djay app (Settings > MIDI > Scan for Bluetooth MIDI Devices > DJControl Mix).

Read more

Mode 2: Monitor tracks like pro DJs do!

. Enable Bluetooth.

2. Connect DJControl Mix to an external battery or power adapter.

3. Connect DJControl Mix to your smartphone via the djay app (Settings > MIDI > Scan for Bluetooth MIDI Devices > DJControl Mix).

4. Connect the splitter cable to your smartphone, headphones

Read more

Technical specifications

smartphones and tablets Requires smartphone or tablet with Bluetooth Low Energy/4.1 or higher Android 8.1 or higher iOS 12.2 or higher
Power supply Powered via USB: plug the device into an electrical outlet using a USB power adapter (not included), or connect it to an external battery (5 V @ 500 mA) to mix anywhere!
djay app Available free of charge on the App Store (iOS) or Google Play (Android)
Dimensions 13.4 x 3.9 x 1.9 inches / 34 x 10 x 4.9 cm (W x D x H)
Box contents DJControl Mix
Phone/tablet stand USB power cable (USB-C to USB-A)

Product Description

The Hercules DJCOntrol Mix allows anyone discover very easily how to mix on smartphones and tablets anywhere, anytime
